IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: WORK WITH THE CITY AND COUNTY OF LOS ANGELES TO BRING MAJOR SPORTING AND ENTERTAINMENT EVENTS TO LOS ANGELES.
IRS990.MissionDesc: WORK WITH THE CITY AND COUNTY OF LOS ANGELES TO BRING MAJOR SPORTING AND ENTERTAINMENT EVENTS TO LOS ANGELES. THESE EVENTS HAVE A SIGNIFICANT ECONOMIC IMPACT ON THE LOCAL ECONOMY AND CONTINUE TO SPOTLIGHT LOS ANGELES AS THE ENTERTAINMENT CAPITAL OF THE WORLD.
IRS990.Desc: MARKETING, PROMOTING AND HOSTING KEY SPORTING AND ENTERTAINMENT EVENTS IN AND AROUND THE COUNTY OF LOS ANGELES.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE ORGANIZATION SERVED AS A FISCAL AGENT FOR THE 2017 USGA AMATEUR GOLF TOURNAMENT HELD IN LOS ANGELES. THE REMAINING FUNDS WILL BE DISBURSED DURING YEAR ENDING JUNE 30, 2019.

LASEC IS EXEMPT FROM FEDERAL AND STATE INCOME TAXES UNDER SECTION 501(C)(3) OF THE INTERNAL REVENUE CODE AND SECTION 23701(D) OF THE CALIFORNIA REVENUE AND TAXATION CODE. THUS, NO PROVISION FOR TAXES IS REFLECTED IN THE ACCOMPANYING STATEMENT OF ACTIVITIES. LASEC HAS ADOPTED FINANCIAL ACCOUNTING STANDARDS BOARD ("FASB") ACCOUNTING STANDARDS CODIFICATION ("ASC") SECTION 740, INCOME TAXES, WHICH CLARIFY THE ACCOUNTING FOR UNCERTAINTY IN INCOME TAXES. FASB ASC 740-10 PESCRIBES A RECOGNITION THRESHOLD AND MEASUREMENT ATTRIBUTE FOR THE FINANCIAL STATEMENT RECOGNITION AND MEASUREMENT OF A TAX POSITION TAKEN OR EXPECTED TO BE TAKE IN A TAX RETURN. FASB ASC 740-10 REQUIRES THAT AN ORGANIZATION RECOGNIZE IN THE FINANCIAL STATEMENTS THE IMPACT OF THE TAX POSITION IF THAT POSITION WILL MORE LIKELY THAN NOT BE SUSTAINED ON AUDIT, BASED ON THE TECHNICAL MERITS OF THE POSITION. AT JUNE 30, 2018 AND FOR THE YEAR THEN ENDED, LASEC HAD NO MATERIAL UNRECOGNIZED TAX BENEFITS, TAX PENALTIES OR INTEREST. LASEC'S FEDERAL FORMS 990, RETURN OF ORGANIZATION EXEMPT FROM INCOME TAX, ARE SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THE IRS, GENERALLY FOR THREE YEARS AFTER THEY ARE FILED, AND REMAIN OPEN FOR THE YEARS ENDED JUNE 30, 2015 THROUGH 2017. THE CALIFORNIA FORM 199, CALIFORNIA EXEMPT ORGANIZATION ANNUAL INFORMATION RETURN, IS SUBJECT TO EXAMINATION BY THE FRANCHISE TAX BOARD, GENERALLY FOR FOUR YEARS AFTER THEY ARE FILED, AND REMAIN OPEN FOR THE YEARS ENDED JUNE 30, 2014 THROUGH 2017.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 11B
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: FORM 990 IS REVIEWED BY THE BOARD CHAIR, TREASURER, PRESIDENT AND ACCEPTED FOR FILING BY THE FINANCE COMMITTEE. THE FORM 990 IS THEN PRESENTED TO THE FULL BOARD PRIOR TO FILING.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 12C
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: BOARD MEMBERS ARE REQUIRED TO ANNUALLY CERTIFY THAT THEY HAVE READ AND UNDERSTOOD THE CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY AND AGREE TO COMPLY WITH ITS TERMS. ANY POTENTIAL CONFLICT OF INTEREST ARE DISCLOSED, AND BOARD MEMBERS ABSTAIN FROM DISCUSSION AND VOTING ON ANY MATTERS THAT MAY BE A CONFLICT.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION B, LINE 15
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: THE CHAIR OF THE BOARD, WITH APPROVAL OF THE BOARD, APPOINTS A COMPENSATION COMMITTEE. THIS COMMITTEE REVIEWS CURRENT SALARIES AND DETERMINES ANY ADJUSTMENTS, TAKING INTO ACCOUNT OTHER ORGANIZATIONS OF SIMILAR SIZE AND NATURE, PERFORMANCE AND THE FINANCIAL CONDITION OF THE ORGANIZATION. FROM TIME TO TIME AN INDEPENDENT COMPENSATION CONSULTANT MAY BE CONSULTED.

SupplementalInformationDetail.FormAndLineReferenceDesc: FORM 990, PART VI, SECTION C, LINE 19
SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: GOVERNING DOCUMENTS, CONFLICT OF INTEREST POLICY, AND FINANCIAL STATEMENTS ARE AVAILABLE UPON WRITTEN REQUEST.
